# Soft-Delete (IsArchived) Conventions

This project never hard-deletes domain data. Every soft-deletable entity inherits `BaseEntity`
(`src/Server/FleetMgmt.Server.Model/BaseEntity.cs`), which carries `IsArchived`.

## Core rules

- **"Delete" means archive.** `EntityRepository<TEntity>.Delete` sets `IsArchived = true` and updates the row. Never call `Set.Remove` for `BaseEntity` types.
- **Archived rows are hidden automatically.** `AppDbContext` applies a global query filter `HasQueryFilter(e => !e.IsArchived)` to every `BaseEntity`. To read archived rows use `EntityRepository.AllQuery` or `.IgnoreQueryFilters()` (e.g. seeding/admin), and remember `.IgnoreQueryFilters()` disables *all* filters.
- **Uniqueness is per non-archived row.** So a code/name can be reused once the old record is archived.

## Filtered unique indexes — do NOT hand-write the IsArchived filter

`AppDbContext.ConfigureArchivedEntityUniqueIndexes` runs after all configurations and automatically
adds `[IsArchived] = 0` (plus `[Col] IS NOT NULL` for nullable indexed columns) to every **unique**
index on a `BaseEntity` type.

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD — just declare the unique index; the [IsArchived] = 0 filter is added centrally
builder.HasIndex(c => c.CountryCode).IsUnique();

// ❌ BAD — never add a manual IsArchived filter; it duplicates/conflicts with the central logic
builder.HasIndex(c => c.CountryCode).IsUnique().HasFilter("[IsArchived] = 0");
```

`HasFilter` is only for non-`BaseEntity` types (e.g. `User.Email IS NOT NULL`).

## DB errors from the filter must surface as a business exception

A duplicate write against an `[IsArchived] = 0` filtered unique index must reach the user as the
localized `SoftDeleteConflictException`, never a raw `DbUpdateException`.

- This is handled centrally in `AppDbContext.SaveChanges`/`SaveChangesAsync` via `SoftDeleteConflictTranslator.TryTranslate`. Do not catch `DbUpdateException` ad-hoc in services to reformat these.
- Messages live in `AppStrings` (`SoftDeleteUniqueConflictException`, `SoftDeleteUniqueConflictWithValueException`) with `en` + `fa` values, and are formatted in `ServerExceptionHandler`. Keep user-facing text clear and free of SQL/index/column names.
- Prefer validating duplicates in the service first (throw `ResourceValidationException`/`ConflictException` with a field-specific message) for the best UX; the translator is the safety net for the rest.

## When you add a new unique index on a soft-deletable entity

1. Declare `.IsUnique()` only (no manual IsArchived filter).
2. Add an EF Core migration and confirm the generated `CreateIndex` includes `filter: "[IsArchived] = 0..."`.
3. Verify the model snapshot has the matching `.HasFilter("[IsArchived] = 0...")`.
4. If the entity is *not* a `BaseEntity`, the filter will not be added automatically — reconsider whether it should be soft-deletable.
